	     Cape Town – A South African woman was found with packets of drugs taped to her body at Cape Town International Airport, Western Cape police said on Wednesday. Police officers in international departures found three compressed packets wrapped in tape under her clothing during a search on Tuesday morning, said Captain FC van Wyk. The 1kg consignment was suspected to be tik (methamphetamine), with an estimated street value of R225 000. The 44-year-old woman would appear in court once charged.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  